---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site, mailLink } from '../data/site';

const a = site.address;
---

<Layout
  current="/privacy-policy"
  title="Privacy Policy - Kensons Garage | Car Body Repair South London"
  description="How Kensons Garage in Brixton handles your personal data under UK GDPR — what we collect, how we use it, and your rights."
  noindex={true}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    crumb="Privacy Policy"
  />

  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="legal-prose fade-in">
        <p><strong>Last updated: June 2026</strong></p>

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how {site.name} collects, uses and protects any personal
          information you provide when you contact us or use this website. We are committed to
          protecting your privacy and handling your data in line with the UK General Data Protection
          Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018. England &amp; Wales.
        </p>

        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          {site.name} is a family-run car body repair business based in Brixton, South London. For the
          purposes of data protection law, we are the <strong>data controller</strong> responsible for
          your personal information.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our contact details are:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>{site.name}</strong></li>
          <li>{a.unit}, {a.street}, {a.area}, {a.city} {a.postcode}</li>
          <li>Email: <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a></li>
          <li>Telephone: {site.phoneMobile} or {site.phoneSecondary}</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What information we collect</h2>
        <p>
          We only collect the information you choose to send us when you make an enquiry — for example
          through the quote form, by WhatsApp, by email or by telephone. This may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your <strong>name</strong>;</li>
          <li>Your <strong>contact details</strong> (such as your phone number and email address);</li>
          <li>Details of your <strong>vehicle</strong> (such as make, model and registration);</li>
          <li>A <strong>description and any photos of the damage</strong> or work you would like us to quote for.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not ask for, and you should not send us, any more information than is needed to provide
          you with a quote and carry out a repair.
        </p>

        <h2>How we use your information</h2>
        <p>
          We use the information you provide solely to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Respond to your enquiry and provide you with an estimate or quote;</li>
          <li>Arrange, book in and carry out repairs or servicing on your vehicle;</li>
          <li>Communicate with you about the work and answer any questions you have;</li>
          <li>Liaise with your insurer where you have asked us to handle a claim on your behalf.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell your information, and we do not use it for marketing without your consent.
        </p>

        <h2>Our lawful basis for processing</h2>
        <p>
          Under the UK GDPR, the lawful bases we rely on for processing your information are:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Taking steps to enter into a contract</strong> — where you ask us for a quote or to
            carry out work, we process your details to provide that quote and perform the repair;
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — to respond to your enquiries and run our business
            efficiently, in a way you would reasonably expect and which does not override your rights.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>This is a static website</h2>
        <p>
          This website is a <strong>static site that stores no personal data on a server</strong>. There
          is no database and no account system. When you use the quote form, it simply opens your own
          email app (or your device's messaging app) with your message pre-filled — your enquiry is sent
          directly from you to us, just as if you had emailed us yourself. We only ever see the information
          you actually choose to send.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          To keep the site useful we rely on a small number of third-party services:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Maps</strong> — we embed a Google map so you can find the workshop. If the map
            loads, Google may receive data such as your IP address and may set its own cookies. Your use
            of Google Maps is subject to Google's own privacy policy.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>WhatsApp</strong> — if you choose to message us on WhatsApp, your message is handled by
            WhatsApp under its own privacy policy. You only share information with WhatsApp if you decide to
            contact us this way.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This site uses essential cookies and a local consent preference only. We do not set tracking
          cookies without your consent. For full details, please see our
          <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>How long we keep your information</h2>
        <p>
          Because this is a static site, we hold no personal data on a server. Any enquiry you send by
          email, WhatsApp or phone is kept only for as long as is necessary to provide your quote, complete
          any repair and meet our legal and accounting obligations (for example, keeping records of work
          carried out and payments received). After that, we securely delete or destroy it.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Under the UK GDPR you have the following rights in relation to your personal data:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>The right to be informed</strong> about how your data is used (this policy);</li>
          <li><strong>The right of access</strong> — to ask for a copy of the information we hold about you;</li>
          <li><strong>The right to rectification</strong> — to have inaccurate information corrected;</li>
          <li><strong>The right to erasure</strong> — to ask us to delete your information;</li>
          <li><strong>The right to restrict processing</strong> in certain circumstances;</li>
          <li><strong>The right to object</strong> to processing based on our legitimate interests;</li>
          <li><strong>The right to data portability</strong> for information you have provided to us.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details below. We will respond
          within one month.
        </p>

        <h2>How to complain</h2>
        <p>
          We hope to resolve any concern you have, so please contact us first. You also have the right to
          complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), the UK supervisory authority for data
          protection. You can reach the ICO at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>
          or by calling their helpline on 0303 123 1113.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please contact us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>{site.name}</strong></li>
          <li>{a.unit}, {a.street}, {a.area}, {a.city} {a.postcode}</li>
          <li>Email: <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a></li>
          <li>Telephone: {site.phoneMobile} or {site.phoneSecondary}</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
